rComments: This was the most difficult class I have taken so far. Slides are difficult to follow because concepts aren't explained clear enough. Tutorials broke down info but it wasn't every week. Assignments are weighed heavy and the exam consisted of 4 questions and no clear study guide. The study guide also had noting to do with the exam.

rComments: Easily one of the best Political Science lecturers at UofT. The content in his lectures is clear and straight-forward, and he goes in-depth on content in his office hours. The exam was challenging but if you go to lectures and study the overall material, you'll be more than fine.

rComments: This prof does not explain well some of the concepts in class, skips over some but then expects students to know it for the exam. Exam instructions were unclear. Only 6 questions or so and did not tell us how much we were expected to write for each. Study guide had a lot of detailed instructions of what to study but none of that was on the exam.
